The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.DS), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses information theory (cs.IT) in the context of designing truthful mechanisms.
